quran[30]{c,v,t,f}:
87,16,"No; but you prefer the present life, {1}",footnotes:1:That is
87,17,"whereas the Hereafter is better and more enduring. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
87,18,"This, indeed, was in the ancient Scrolls,"
87,19,"the Scrolls of Abraham and Moses. {1}",footnotes:1:This is the second place in the Quran where reference has been made to the teachings of the Books of the Prophets Abraham and Moses (peace be upon them). The first reference was made in section 3 of Surah An-Najm.
88,1,"Has the news of the overwhelming event reached you? {1}",footnotes:1:The overwhelming: the Resurrection which will overshadow the whole world. One should know that here the Hereafter as a whole is being depicted
88,2,"Some faces {1} that Day shall be downcast with fear,",footnotes:1:Some faces: some persons
88,3,"be toiling and worn-out;"
88,4,"they shall burn in a Scorching Fire;"
88,5,"their drink shall be from a boiling spring."
88,6,"They shall have no food except bitter dry thorns {1}",footnotes:1:At some places in the Quran
88,7,"that will neither nourish nor satisfy their hunger."
88,8,"On that very Day some faces shall be radiant with joy,"
88,9,"well-pleased with their striving. {1}",footnotes:1:That is: they will be overjoyed to see the best results in the Hereafter of their endeavors and deeds in the world; they will be satisfied to see that they had
88,10,"They will be in a lofty Garden"
88,11,"wherein they shall hear no vain talk. {1}",footnotes:1:This thing has been mentioned at several places in the Quran as a major blessing of Paradise. (For explanation
(E.N. 21 of Surah An-Naba).
88,12,"In it there shall be a flowing spring,"
88,13,"and couches raised high,"
88,14,"and goblets laid out, {1}",footnotes:1:That is
88,15,"and cushions arrayed in rows,"
88,16,"and rich carpets levelled out."
88,17,"Do (these unbelievers) not observe the camels: how they were created?"
88,18,"And the sky: how it was raised high?"
88,19,"And the mountains: how they were fixed?"
88,20,"And the earth: how it was spread out? {1}",footnotes:1:That is
88,21,"So render good counsel, for you are simply required to counsel,"
88,22,"and are not invested with the authority to compel them. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
88,23,"But whoever will turn away (from the Truth),"
88,24,"Allah will chastise him with the most terrible chastisement."
88,25,"Surely to Us is their return;"
88,26,"and then it is for Us to call them to account."
